cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the task of texture segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of self-supervised learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of synthetic data sets, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the generalization of the model to natural images and videos, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
